					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">There are two components to square wave phase: the state of the period divider (by 8+1 through 2047+1), and the state of the 8-step counter. As I understand it, a note-on on the Game Boy resets only the period divider, but a note-on ($4003/$4007 write) on the NES resets only the state of the 8-step counter. And you can't force a full reset of the period divider by setting the period to zero because the length counter logic treats periods less than 8+1 as note-off. Am I right?</div>

